    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER PSO140-61 - DISASSEMBLE -
        SHIFTER HOUSING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="9">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Shifter Housing Forward Control</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301403">Figure 3</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301403" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301403" filename="../figg13/G1301403.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Shifter Housing Forward Control Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Shifter Housing Center Control</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301404">Figure 4</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301404" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301404" filename="../figg13/G1301404.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Shifter Housing Center Control Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the cover on the bench with the forks in the neutral position, and remove the oil
                    trough (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301405">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301405" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301405" filename="../figg13/G1301405.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5. Remove Oil Trough</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 5th-6th bracket set screw. Rotate fork and rod approximately 90 degrees (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301406">Figure 6</hotlnk>). Note the location of the interlock pin which must
                    remain in a vertical position while removing rod to prevent damage to the shift bracket spring.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301406" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301406" filename="../figg13/G1301406.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 6. Rotate Fork and Rod</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Continue disassembly by removing 5th-6th fork set screw and remove rod toward the rear
                    of the cover (Forward Control: remove rod toward front of cover) (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301407">Figure 7</hotlnk>). Recover interlock poppets and pin, also shift bracket
                    plunger, spring and ball.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301407" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301407" filename="../figg13/G1301407.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7. Remove 5th-6th Fork Set Screw</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 4th fork and bracket bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301408">Figure 8</hotlnk>). As the shift rod is pulled from the cover, be sure not
                    to lose the interlock pin and poppet.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301408" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301408" filename="../figg13/G1301408.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8. Remove 4th Fork and Bracket Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">In the same manner, remove 2nd-3rd fork set screw, fork and rod from cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301409">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301409" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301409" filename="../figg13/G1301409.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9. Remove 2nd-3rd Fork Set Screw</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 1st-Rev. fork and bracket to complete the disassembly of the shifter housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301410">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301410" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301410" filename="../figg13/G1301410.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10. Remove 1st-Reverse Fork and Bracket</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check shifter housing for any signs of abnormal wear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301411">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301411" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301411" filename="../figg13/G1301411.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11. Inspect Shifter Housing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
